{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882695064,"sessionID":"ses_28524b697ffeTsmQ13eGzrEk2C","part":{"id":"prt_d7adb6a07001Od4Rd5sdfNyzkP","messageID":"msg_d7adb5a400011ZuTJ9DqOddYGm","sessionID":"ses_28524b697ffeTsmQ13eGzrEk2C","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-15a5c7f39c7a4a608cd04f0d02ad6605","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/AR-031-IMPLEMENTATION-SUMMARY.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/AR-031-IMPLEMENTATION-SUMMARY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031: RBAC Configuration Implementation Summary\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: AR-031 implements the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration for the AgentCube platform. This module provides ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources for all platform components.\n6: \n7: **Module:** `manifests`\n8: **Language:** YAML (Helm templates)\n9: **Status:** ✅ COMPLETE\n10: \n11: ## Implementation Details\n12: \n13: ### Files Created/Modified\n14: \n15: #### Templates (Existing)\n16: All RBAC templates were already implemented and follow the design specification:\n17: \n18: 1. **ServiceAccount Templates**\n19:    - `templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n20:    - `templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n21:    - `templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml`\n22: \n23: 2. **RBAC Templates**\n24:    - `templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml` (Role + RoleBinding)\n25:    - `templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml` (ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding)\n26:    - `templates/router/rbac.yaml` (Role + RoleBinding)\n27: \n28: 3. **Helper Templates**\n29:    - `templates/_helpers.tpl` (ServiceAccount name helpers)\n30: \n31: #### Configuration (Existing)\n32: - `values.yaml` - Complete RBAC configuration structure\n33: \n34: #### Tests (NEW - Created in this implementation)\n35: \n36: ##### Unit Tests\n37: - `tests/rbac_test.yaml` - Comprehensive Helm template tests (24 test cases)\n38: \n39: ##### Integration Tests\n40: - `tests/integration/test_workload_manager_permissions.sh` - Verify workload-manager can create pods\n41: - `tests/integration/test_router_permissions.sh` - Verify router can list secrets\n42: - `tests/integration/test_controller_manager_permissions.sh` - Verify controller-manager cannot delete pods\n43: - `tests/integration/test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh` - Deploy with custom RBAC rules\n44: - `tests/integration/test_existing_serviceaccount.sh` - Deploy with existing ServiceAccount\n45: \n46: ##### Security Tests\n47: - `tests/integration/test_least_privilege.sh` - Verify principle of least privilege\n48: - `tests/integration/test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh` - Check for wildcard permissions\n49: - `tests/integration/test_token_automount.sh` - Verify token automount configuration\n50: \n51: ##### Documentation\n52: - `tests/README.md` - Comprehensive test documentation\n53: \n54: ## RBAC Architecture\n55: \n56: ### Component Permissions\n57: \n58: | Component | ServiceAccount | Role/ClusterRole | Scope | Permissions |\n59: |-----------|---------------|------------------|-------|-------------|\n60: | controller-manager | `agentcube` | Role | Namespace | Custom rules (empty by default) |\n61: | workload-manager | `agentcube-workload-manager` | ClusterRole | Cluster | CRDs, pods, services, configmaps, secrets, events |\n62: | router | `agentcube-router` | Role | Namespace | Secrets (get, list, watch) |\n63: \n64: ### Workload Manager ClusterRole Rules\n65: \n66: ```yaml\n67: # CRD resources\n68: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n69:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n70:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n71: \n72: # CRD status\n73: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n74:   resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n75:   verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n76: \n77: # Core resources\n78: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n79:   resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\", \"secrets\"]\n80:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n81: \n82: # Pod status\n83: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n84:   resources: [\"pods/status\"]\n85:   verbs: [\"get\"]\n86: \n87: # Events\n88: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n89:   resources: [\"events\"]\n90:   verbs: [\"create\", \"patch\"]\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ### Router Role Rules\n94: \n95: ```yaml\n96: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n97:   resources: [\"secrets\"]\n98:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### Controller Manager Role Rules\n102: \n103: ```yaml\n104: # Empty by default - custom rules can be added via values.yaml\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ## Configuration Options\n108: \n109: ### Enable/Disable RBAC\n110: \n111: ```yaml\n112: controllerManager:\n113:   rbac:\n114:     create: true\n115: \n116: workloadManager:\n117:   rbac:\n118:     create: true\n119: \n120: router:\n121:   rbac:\n122:     create: true\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ### Custom ServiceAccount Names\n126: \n127: ```yaml\n128: controllerManager:\n129:   serviceAccount:\n130:     name: custom-controller-sa\n131: \n132: workloadManager:\n133:   serviceAccount:\n134:     name: custom-workload-sa\n135: \n136: router:\n137:   serviceAccount:\n138:     name: custom-router-sa\n139: ```\n140: \n141: ### Use Existing ServiceAccounts\n142: \n143: ```yaml\n144: controllerManager:\n145:   serviceAccount:\n146:     create: false\n147:     name: existing-sa\n148: ```\n149: \n150: ### Custom RBAC Rules\n151: \n152: ```yaml\n153: controllerManager:\n154:   rbac:\n155:     rules:\n156:       - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n157:         resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n158:         verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n159: ```\n160: \n161: ### ServiceAccount Annotations\n162: \n163: ```yaml\n164: controllerManager:\n165:   serviceAccount:\n166:     annotations:\n167:       eks.amazonaws.com/role-arn: arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/my-role\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ## Testing\n171: \n172: ### Unit Tests\n173: \n174: Run all unit tests:\n175: ```bash\n176: helm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube\n177: ```\n178: \n179: Run specific test file:\n180: ```bash\n181: helm unittest ./manifests/charts/agentcube -f tests/rbac_test.yaml\n182: ```\n183: \n184: **Test Coverage:**\n185: - ✅ All RBAC resources are created when enabled\n186: - ✅ RBAC resources are skipped when disabled\n187: - ✅ Existing ServiceAccounts are used when configured\n188: - ✅ Custom RBAC rules are applied correctly\n189: - ✅ Labels and annotations are applied correctly\n190: - ✅ Naming conventions are followed\n191: - ✅ Role/ClusterRole bindings reference correct ServiceAccounts\n192: - ✅ Namespace configuration works correctly\n193: - ✅ Component disable works correctly\n194: \n195: ### Integration Tests\n196: \n197: ```bash\n198: # Permission verification\n199: ./tests/integration/test_workload_manager_permissions.sh agentcube\n200: ./tests/integration/test_router_permissions.sh agentcube\n201: ./tests/integration/test_controller_manager_permissions.sh agentcube\n202: \n203: # End-to-end tests\n204: ./tests/integration/test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh\n205: ./tests/integration/test_existing_serviceaccount.sh\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ### Security Tests\n209: \n210: ```bash\n211: ./tests/integration/test_least_privilege.sh agentcube\n212: ./tests/integration/test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh agentcube\n213: ./tests/integration/test_token_automount.sh agentcube\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ## Security Features\n217: \n218: ### Principle of Least Privilege\n219: - Router has minimal permissions (secrets only)\n220: - Controller Manager has no default permissions\n221: - Workload Manager requires cluster-wide access but is bounded to specific resources\n222: \n223: ### No Wildcard Permissions\n224: - All permissions use explicit verbs (no `*`)\n225: - Tests verify no wildcard permissions exist\n226: \n227: ### ServiceAccount Security\n228: - Each component uses dedicated ServiceAccount\n229: - Names follow consistent naming convention\n230: - Token automount can be controlled via pod spec\n231: \n232: ### Namespace Isolation\n233: - All namespace-scoped resources use correct namespace\n234: - Role bindings only authorize access within same namespace\n235: - Only workload-manager uses cluster-wide resources\n236: \n237: ## Compliance with Design Document\n238: \n239: The implementation fully complies with the design document:\n240: \n241: ✅ **ServiceAccount Templates**\n242: - Controller-Manager SA with correct labels and annotations\n243: - Workload-Manager SA with correct labels and annotations\n244: - Router SA with correct labels and annotations\n245: \n246: ✅ **Role Templates**\n247: - Controller-Manager Role with empty rules by default\n248: - Router Role with secrets-only permissions\n249: - Custom rules support via values.yaml\n250: \n251: ✅ **ClusterRole Template**\n252: - Workload-Manager ClusterRole with all required permissions\n253: - CRD permissions (agentruntimes, codeinterpreters)\n254: - Core resource permissions (pods, services, configmaps, secrets)\n255: - Status and event permissions\n256: \n257: ✅ **RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding Templates**\n258: - Correct bindings between SAs and Roles/ClusterRoles\n259: - Proper namespace references\n260: - Correct roleRef configurations\n261: \n262: ✅ **Helper Templates**\n263: - `agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName`\n264: - `agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName`\n265: - `agentcube.router.serviceAccountName`\n266: \n267: ✅ **Values Configuration**\n268: - Complete RBAC configuration structure\n269: - ClusterRole rules defined\n270: - Component-specific RBAC settings\n271: \n272: ✅ **Tests**\n273: - Comprehensive unit tests (24 test cases)\n274: - Integration tests (5 test scripts)\n275: - Security tests (3 test scripts)\n276: - Test documentation\n277: \n278: ## Acceptance Criteria Status\n279: \n280: | Criteria | Status | Notes |\n281: |----------|--------|-------|\n282: | ServiceAccount templates exist and follow naming convention | ✅ | All three components have SA templates |\n283: | Role templates exist with correct permissions | ✅ | Controller-manager and router roles |\n284: | ClusterRole template exists with all required permissions | ✅ | Workload-manager cluster role |\n285: | RoleBinding templates bind SAs to correct Roles | ✅ | All bindings correctly configured |\n286: | ClusterRoleBinding template binds SA to ClusterRole | ✅ | Workload-manager binding |\n287: | Helper templates generate correct SA names | ✅ | Three helper templates defined |\n288: | Values configuration supports all options | ✅ | Complete structure in values.yaml |\n289: | Unit tests cover all RBAC resources | ✅ | 24 test cases |\n290: | Integration tests verify permissions | ✅ | 5 integration test scripts |\n291: | Security tests verify best practices | ✅ | 3 security test scripts |\n292: | Documentation is complete | ✅ | Comprehensive test README |\n293: \n294: ## Future Enhancements\n295: \n296: As outlined in the design document:\n297: \n298: 1. **Pod Security Policy Support** - Add PSP resources for enhanced pod security\n299: 2. **NetworkPolicy RBAC** - Add network policies to restrict inter-component communication\n300: 3. **Dynamic RBAC Management** - Support for dynamic RBAC rule updates\n301: 4. **Audit Logging** - Add audit annotations to RBAC resources\n302: 5. **Multi-Tenant Support** - Namespace-specific RBAC overrides\n303: 6. **RBAC Testing Automation** - Automated permission testing in CI/CD\n304: 7. **ServiceAccount Token Rotation** - Support for token rotation policies\n305: 8. **External RBAC Integration** - OIDC-based service account authentication\n306: \n307: ## References\n308: \n309: - [Design Document](../design.md)\n310: - [Helm Chart Documentation](./README.md)\n311: - [Test Documentation](./tests/README.md)\n312: - [Kubernetes RBAC Documentation](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/)\n313: \n314: ## Conclusion\n315: \n316: AR-031 RBAC configuration is fully implemented and tested. All templates, configuration, and tests are in place and follow the design specification. The implementation provides:\n317: \n318: - ✅ Complete RBAC configuration for all three components\n319: - ✅ Comprehensive unit tests (24 test cases)\n320: - ✅ Integration tests for permission verification\n321: - ✅ Security tests for best practices\n322: - ✅ Complete documentation\n323: \n324: The RBAC configuration is production-ready and follows Kubernetes security best practices.\n\n(End of file - total 324 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031: RBAC Configuration Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-031 implements the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration for the AgentCube platform. This module provides ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources for all platform components.\n\n**Module:** `manifests`\n**Language:** YAML (Helm templates)\n**Status:** ✅ COMPLETE\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Files Created/Modified\n\n#### Templates (Existing)\nAll RBAC templates were already implemented and follow the design specification:\n\n1. **ServiceAccount Templates**\n   - `templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n   - `templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/AR-031-IMPLEMENTATION-SUMMARY.md","time":{"start":1775882695038,"end":1775882695062}}}}
